                    <history><origin>Possibly completed in <origPlace cert="medium" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000235">Greater Iran</origPlace>; undated, but possibly <date cert="medium">14th century CE</date>.</origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Formerly owned by one <persName role="ins aut seal fmo">Muḥammad Rashīd</persName> as per his seal impression on <locus from="4a" to="4a">4a</locus> and adjacent inscriptions there and on <locus from="1a" to="1a">1a</locus>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance><p>Subsequently acquired Syrian scholar and translator <persName role="fmo seal" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/2457671" key="person_2457671">Jibrā'īl bin Yūsuf al-Mukhalla‘ (d. 1851)</persName> as per his seal impression and adjacent notation on folio <locus from="1a" to="1a">1a</locus>, then auctioned together with the rest of his library in <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7002261">Damascus</placeName> in <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1920">1920</date>.</p></provenance>
                        <provenance><p>Evidently obtained by <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7011781">London</placeName> antiquarian booksellers and publishers <persName role="bsl" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/135465378" key="person_135465378">Luzac &amp; Co.</persName>.</p></provenance>
